lgorithms for identifying the frequency (wavelength), amplitude, location and phase (stimulation sequence) of magnetic field waves on specialized conductive tissue and muscle tissue; and methods for separating of these signals from each other; and also uses the signal collecting and data storage algorithms to create the 3D map of the conduction system; and the computer where the 3D map will be created; and the monitor that reflects the generated 3D map and the hardware requi red for the system i n whi ch al I equi pment works together. 2. The special hybrid signal collector catheter according to claim 1, which comprises an apparatus (1), that is located at proximal of the hybrid catheter and allows the electrophysiologic to move the distal tip of the catheter, which reaches into the heart through the vessel from outside the patient (rotation, flexion and change of the diameter of the distal ring, catheter back and forth movement), the catheter trunk (shaft) length (2) is enough to be extended it into the heart from the inguinal region (femoral vein and artery) of the patient, data cables (6) to provide connectivity to the 

